  "texts": [
    "This section reviews to what extent the PLD Proposal addresses these problems.",
    "The PLD Proposal keeps the consumer-expectation test despite the concerns discussed in this paper: The test does not include a risk/utility-analysis, and consumer expectations of AI may well be inaccurate or unreasonable.",
    "Others have also noted the difficulty in applying the consumer expectation test to assess the defectiveness of AI (Borghetti, 2019; De Bruyne et al., 2023).",
    "91 The proposal does not settle whether a risk/utility-analysis is allowed (Veldt, 2023, 26).",
    "While some note that, in practice, 89 If physicians do not check each flagged positive from the AI tool, they might be held liable for not acting on a suspected diagnosis."
  ],
